# Rule 07 — Target architecture (migration north star)

Complements Rule 01 (zero-downtime) and Rule 02 (core stack). During transition, legacy paths may remain behind feature flags until parity gates pass.

## 1. Remove `web-service/` entirely

- No new code under `web-service/`.
- Any touch to legacy handlers must plan an internal replacement in `ez_core` or theme bridge with a removal ticket.
- Delete the folder only when `grep` shows zero runtime references (theme, core, cron).
- Keep nginx `410` on `/web-service/reservation.php` after HTTP removal.

## 2. Medoo → Eloquent only in core

- Theme: no new `medoo()` / `medoo_queries()` usage; migrate to `ez_core` Models/Repositories.
- Booking/search hot paths: `CapsuleManager` + `external` connection for `escapezo_queries`.
- Helpers: `ez_table()`, `ez_external_table()` in `ez_core/src/Support/database-helpers.php`.

## 3. Modular + zero coupling

- Features live under `ez_core/src/Modules/{Name}/`.
- Modules register via their own `*Module::register()` from `Bootstrap`.
- Failure in one module must not break unrelated modules (avoid hard requires of theme `saeed-codes` from core; use interfaces or WP hooks).

## 4. Design patterns

- Document pattern per class in `docs/project/architecture/design-patterns.md`.
- Gateway: Front Controller + Action.
- Domain: Application Service + Repository.
- Legacy: Adapter (temporary only).

## 5. Folder structure + deploy

- PSR-4 `EscapeZoom\Core\` under `ez_core/src/`.
- Theme: `assets/` source, `dist/` built assets (Vite).
- Future: `build-final.sh` produces a `final/` tree (minified CSS/JS, no `node_modules`) for production upload — see P6 roadmap.

## Feature flags (booking example)

- `EZ_BOOKING_USE_INTERNAL` — dispatch without HTTP loopback.
- `EZ_BOOKING_READ_ELOQUENT` (future) — read sans via Eloquent service instead of `LegacySansAdapter`.
